 <body>
  <p>To create a test environment (sandbox mode), apply the following steps:</p> 
  <note>
    Only use this environment creation method for test environments. In all other cases, use the target mapping wizard. For more on this, refer to 
   <a href="../../interaction/using/creating-a-test-environment.md#creating-an-offer-environment" target="_blank">Creating an offer environment</a>.
   <br /> 
  </note>
  <ol>
   <li><p>Launch the Adobe Campaign explorer and go to the instance root.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Right-click and add a <strong>Generic folder</strong> using the drop-down menus.</p> <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/offer_env_creation_001.png" title="offer_env_creation_001.png" /></li>
   <li><p>Next, go to the folder you just created and add an <strong>Offer environment</strong> using the right-click menus.</p> <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/offer_env_creation_001bis.png" title="offer_env_creation_001bis.png" /></li>
   <li><p>Apply the same process to create the environment sub-folders and elements. </p> </li>
   <li><p>Once your tests have finished and you wish to use the environment in production, duplicate the offers and spaces in your design environment. (Right-click &gt; <strong>Actions</strong> &gt; <strong>Deploy</strong>).</p> <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/migration_interaction_5.png" title="migration_interaction_5.png" /></li>
  </ol>
 </body>
